Spinach Cheese:
* 7 oz spinach (200 g)
* 3 garlic cloves
* salt, pepper to taste
* 2/3 cup dairy-free cream cheese or cashew ricotta recipe
* 3/4 cup dairy-free cheese (75 g) shredded
Roasted mushrooms:
* 1 tbsp olive oil
* 5 oz mushrooms (150 g)
* salt to taste
Topping:
* 2 tbsp pine nuts
Cashew Ricotta:
* 250 g of cashew nuts
* 50 ml of water
* 2-3 tbsp of nutritional yeast flakes
* 1 small clove of garlic
* 2 tbsp of lemon juice
* salt
* pepper
1. Heat your oven to 200¬∞C. 
2. Roll out your pizza dough with a rolling pin. Place the pizza dough onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
4. Cook spinach for 1-2 minutes until it starts to wilt. Then squeeze / chop roughly.
5. Heat up a little oil in a small pan / roast garlic for 30 seconds while stirring & add cream cheese or cashew ricotta along with the spinach. Season with salt and pepper.
6. Spread the spinach cream mixture over your pizza dough followed by vegan cheese.
7. Bake the pizza for about 10-15 minutes until cheese is melted.
8. In the meantime, fry mushrooms in a pan with some oil for 6-8 minutes. 
9. Toast pine nuts in another pan without adding any oil.
10. When your pizza is done top with mushrooms and pine nuts if using.
Instructions for Ricotta:
1. Soak the cashew nuts for at least 4 hours (or better overnight). 
2. Then rinse the soaked cashew nuts and blend with all the other ingredients in a food processor. 
Pulse until you get a ricotta-like texture.

-LX3kgl7KSQvuauQTYBd.text:
Austi Pool survived the tourist storm: 
I thought it would be nice to post an image of this beautiful tidal pool in the quiet of a normal working day. I wondered how it would recover after being packed to the hilt with people from all over during the Christmas period. The density of people was a shock to the locals but of course everyone needs to cool down on a hot day! But what was really hard to swallow was the sheer volume of rubbish left all over this normally pristine beach. Soft drink cans & take away food containers galore. I wanted to cry. What is the point of coming to enjoy a beautiful place, yet leaving it like a trash heap? A huge thank you to everyone who helped return the beach to its former glory. 

#lovenature #keepourbeachesclean #respect #respectüåè #üåä

Brilliant take away cup alternative! This is a Huskee cup made from coffee husk "an organic waste material that's produced at the milling stage of coffee production". Apparently I'm helping to recycle hundreds of tonnes of waste material from the production of coffee, so that's good news. The trouble is, it is now served instead of the ceramic cups I used to like at my fav cafe. This is purely aesthetic but has changed the experience somewhat. I like them as a takeaway solution (cafes can participate in a 'trade it for a clean one' Huskeeswap scheme if you bring your own)...but I miss being served a ceramic cup. These feel temporary. Solid, but still temporary... Coffee drinking has become such a ritual! Is it ok to have such a preference? 
Have you tried one?
https://huskee.co/swap/
